@c ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@cindex overview
@cindex polyglot binary

@command{oci2bin} converts any Docker or OCI image into a single,
self-contained ELF64 executable.  The output requires only @command{tar}
on the target machine—no Docker daemon, no container runtime, no
installation.

The output file is also a valid POSIX tar archive accepted by
@command{docker load}, making it a polyglot binary (@pxref{How It
Works}).

@example
oci2bin alpine:latest      # produces ./alpine_latest
./alpine_latest            # runs the container
docker load < alpine_latest
@end example

Containers run rootlessly using Linux user namespaces.  The process
appears as UID@tie{}0 inside the container; on the host it runs as the
invoking user with no elevated privileges.

@quotation Note
This manual covers the core workflow.  The complete and authoritative
reference is the project @file{README} and the documentation site under
@file{docs/}, which always track the current feature set (including the
@option{--restart}, @option{--health}, @option{--gpus}/@option{--cdi-device},
@option{--profile}, and @option{--compress-binary} options, Rekor signing, and
the @command{oci2bin up}/@command{down}/@command{stack} declarative-stack
commands).
@end quotation

@c ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@node Feature Reference
@chapter Feature Reference

A categorized list of every option and capability. Later chapters cover the
common ones in depth; the @file{README} and @file{docs/} site are the
exhaustive reference.

@section Build inputs and transformations

@table @code
@item IMAGE / IMAGE@@sha256:DIGEST
Build from a tag or a validated content digest (the digest is verified;
mismatch aborts).
@item --oci-dir DIR / --tar FILE
Build from an OCI layout dir or a saved tar instead of pulling.
@item --pull-with docker|podman|skopeo
Force the pull backend for the default @code{IMAGE} build (auto-detect order:
docker, podman, skopeo). @code{skopeo} pulls daemonlessly, so no container
engine is required; it does not support @option{--layer}, @option{--offline-only},
or cosign verification.
@item --arch x86_64|aarch64|all
Cross-compile (both directions) or emit a multi-arch wrapper.
@item --add-file H:C / --add-dir H:C
Inject files/directories as a build-time layer.
@item --layer IMAGE
Overlay additional image layers (last image's config wins).
@item --strip / --strip-prefix P / --strip-auto
Remove docs/locales/caches; auto-detect package-manager caches.
@item --squash
Merge all layers into one squashed layer.
@item --compress none|gzip|zstd
Per-layer compression codec.
@item --compress-binary zstd
Recompress the whole payload as one zstd frame (opaque to docker load).
@item --entrypoint VALUE / --cmd VALUE
Override the embedded Entrypoint/Cmd (JSON array or shell-split).
@item --label K=V
Add image-config labels (matchable by ps/list --filter).
@item --cache / --no-cache
Output-binary cache; per-layer cache toggle.
@item --reproducible / --offline-only
Byte-identical output; air-gap seal (no registry fetch, hermetic marker).
@item --pin-digest auto|ALGO:auto|ALGO:HEX
Embed a digest the loader re-checks at run time.
@item --self-update-url URL
Embed a signed-update-manifest URL.
@item --embed-loader-layer / --embed-loader-labels
Persist the loader in the image so @code{reconstruct} can rebuild it.
@end table

@section Signing, attestation, and encryption

@table @code
@item --verify-cosign / --require-cosign / --cosign-key K
Verify the source image's cosign signature before building.
@item --require-signed PUB
Embed a self-enforcing signature policy (refuse to run unsigned).
@item --encrypt --recipient PUB / --recipients-file F
Encrypt the payload to age recipients (opaque at rest).
@item --passphrase [--password-file F]
Symmetric (scrypt) encryption.
@end table

(See also the @code{sign}, @code{verify}, and @code{attest} subcommands, with
@option{--rekor} for a transparency-log entry and @option{--attest} for SLSA/
in-toto provenance.)

@section Runtime: command, filesystem, networking

@table @code
@item --entrypoint / --workdir / -e K=V / --env-file F
Override entrypoint, workdir, environment.
@item -v H:C / --tmpfs P / --read-only / --overlay-persist DIR
Bind mounts, tmpfs, read-only rootfs, persistent overlay upper layer.
@item --secret H[:C] / --secret tpm2:NAME / --ssh-agent
File secrets (memfd_secret-backed), TPM2-sealed secrets, SSH-agent forwarding.
@item --device /dev/H[:C] / --gpus all|N|CDI / --cdi-device KIND=DEV / --no-host-dev
Expose device nodes, GPUs/CDI devices, or skip the host /dev nodes.
@item --net host|none|slirp|pasta|container:PID / -p H:C / --allow-egress H:P
Network modes, published ports, default-deny egress allowlist.
@item --dns IP / --dns-search D / --add-host H:IP / --ipc container:PID
Custom DNS, /etc/hosts entries, shared IPC namespace.
@item --hostname N / --user UID[:GID]
UTS hostname; run as a numeric user.
@end table

@section Runtime: isolation, limits, supervision, observability

@table @code
@item --cap-drop / --cap-add / --no-seccomp / --seccomp-profile F / --gen-seccomp F / --seccomp-deny-write P
Capability and seccomp controls; generate a least-privilege profile.
@item --landlock / --no-landlock / --security-opt apparmor=|label=
Landlock sandbox (auto by default); AppArmor/SELinux confinement.
@item --memory / --cpus / --pids-limit / --ulimit T=N / --size NAME
cgroup v2 limits, setrlimit, and resource presets.
@item --profile dev|prod|locked-down
Apply a bundle of runtime defaults.
@item --init / --detach / --name N / -it
Init reaper, background detach, naming, interactive TTY.
@item --restart no|on-failure[:N]|always|unless-stopped
Supervise and relaunch the workload.
@item --health [--health-cmd C] [--health-interval/-timeout/-retries/-start-period] / --no-health
Run the image HEALTHCHECK; restart on unhealthy when paired with --restart.
@item --metrics-socket P / --notify URL [--notify-name N] / --audit-log F / --clock-offset S
Prometheus metrics socket, lifecycle notifications, JSON audit log, time-namespace clock offset.
@item --vm [--vmm VMM] [--memory/--cpus]
Run inside a hardware-isolated microVM (libkrun or cloud-hypervisor).
@end table

