@node Getting Started
@chapter Getting Started

@cindex installation
@cindex dependencies

@section Build Dependencies

@table @asis
@item Arch Linux
@code{sudo pacman -S gcc python3 docker}
@item Fedora
@code{sudo dnf install gcc glibc-static python3 docker}
@item Debian / Ubuntu
@code{sudo apt install gcc libc6-dev python3 docker.io}
@item openSUSE Tumbleweed
@code{sudo zypper install gcc glibc-devel-static python3 docker}
@item NixOS / nix-shell
@code{nix-shell -p gcc python3 docker}
@end table

@section Installation

@example
git clone https://github.com/latedeployment/oci2bin
cd oci2bin
make          # compile the loader into build/
make install  # install to /usr/local (override with PREFIX=~/.local)
@end example

After installation @command{oci2bin} is on your @env{PATH}.  To use it
without installing, run it directly from the repository root.

@section Quick Start

@example
oci2bin alpine:latest        # output: ./alpine_latest
./alpine_latest               # run default entrypoint
./alpine_latest /bin/ls /etc  # override command
oci2bin nginx:1.25 my-nginx  # explicit output name
@end example

