@node Running Containers
@chapter Running Containers

By default the binary executes the image's configured entrypoint,
equivalent to @command{docker run @var{IMAGE}}.  Arguments after the
binary name replace the default command:

@example
./alpine_latest                          # default entrypoint
./alpine_latest /bin/ls /etc             # override CMD
./alpine_latest /bin/sh -c 'uname -a'
./alpine_latest -- -v                    # '--' ends option parsing
@end example

